        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="Roboto"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">
            Bain Outbids KKR for Fuji Soft
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-oct-14-2.jpg"
          alt="Bain Outbids KKR for Fuji Soft"
        />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">In a competitive bid, Bain Capital has <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/international/2024/10/12/bain-makes-binding-offer-for-fuji-soft-outbidding-kkr-by-7/" target="_blank">outmaneuvered</a> KKR to acquire Japan-based Fuji Soft, offering ¥9,450 per share, 7% higher than KKR’s bid. Bain’s move is part of a growing trend of increased M&A activity in Japan, fueled by a weaker yen and an emphasis on boosting shareholder value. If successful, Bain will take the software developer private, with Fuji Soft’s founding family retaining a minority stake. KKR remains confident in its offer but faces tough competition as Bain seeks to close the deal by the end of October.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 12px"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
