        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">
            Hedge Funds Slash Brent Shorts Amid Risks
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Hedge funds have rapidly cut their <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/10/11/hedge-funds-dump-bets-against-brent-at-fastest-pace-in-8-years/" target="_blank">bearish</a> bets against Brent crude prices, marking the fastest pace in almost eight years. Amid rising geopolitical tensions, including potential retaliatory action by Israel against Iran, investors are uneasy about betting against oil prices. As a result, hedge funds reduced short positions on Brent by nearly 50,000 contracts, signaling caution. Bullish bets on Brent and WTI oil have also surged as speculators expect prices to rise further. The situation remains fluid as global events continue to influence the oil market.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 12px"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
